Sentencas: In this analysis, we report an in-house model to describe the complex fundamental and functional interactions between various internal physico-chemical phenomena of a SOEC.
Titulo: A mathematical model to analyze solid oxide electrolyzer cells (SOECs) for hydrogen production

Sentencas: Electrochemistry at the three-phase boundary is modeled using a modified Butler-Volmer approach that considers H-2 as the electrochemically active species.
Titulo: A mathematical model to analyze solid oxide electrolyzer cells (SOECs) for hydrogen production

Sentencas: Also, a multi step elementary heterogeneous reaction mechanism for the thermo-catalytic H-2 electrode chemistry, dusty-gas model to account for multi component diffusion through porous media, and plug flow model for flow through the channels are used.
Titulo: A mathematical model to analyze solid oxide electrolyzer cells (SOECs) for hydrogen production

Sentencas: Results pertaining to detailed chemical processes within the cathode, electrochemical behavior and irreversible losses during SOEC operation are demonstrated.
Titulo: A mathematical model to analyze solid oxide electrolyzer cells (SOECs) for hydrogen production

Sentencas: Furthermore, efficiency analysis is performed and limiting current behavior of the SOEC system is investigated.
Titulo: A mathematical model to analyze solid oxide electrolyzer cells (SOECs) for hydrogen production
